    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">The jump from transformer to LLM is primarily one of scale: billions of parameters, trillions of tokens, thousands of GPUs. Emergent abilities (chain-of-thought reasoning, code generation, tool use) appear at scale thresholds that we can't predict from smaller models. Whether this is true emergence or smooth scaling is debated. What's not debated: the practical capabilities are real. Whether scale alone produces <a href="https://june.kim/general-intelligence"><img src="/reading/jk.png" alt="jk" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>general intelligence</a> is a separate question &mdash; one that depends on whether the system has a closed consolidation loop, not just a larger forward pass.</p>

